The paper deals with algorithms for computing the largest independent set of polygons, which is a problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses sparsity conditions and intersection graphs, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). The algorithmic techniques used in the paper involve dynamic programming and approximation algorithms, which are common in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
